<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,151,1292]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[333,461,223,247]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.15" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.8" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" unit="mm" value="7.15" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="6.8">6.8–7.5mm</quantity>
long; orange yellow pronotum, MS and MP; head between eyes yellow; deflexed elytral apex pointed; LO entire in V7; abdomen with dimple and hump; distinguished from all but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1253,1389,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminea">
<emphasis box="[1253,1389,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">M. fulminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1976" box="[151,268,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amilae">
<emphasis box="[151,268,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">M. amilae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the possession of pointed elytral apices, and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[908,1006,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminea">
<emphasis box="[908,1006,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">fulminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1976" box="[1068,1144,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amilae">
<emphasis box="[1068,1144,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">amilae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the orange head, and apparent restriction of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne" authorityYear="1987" box="[405,506,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effulgens">
<emphasis box="[405,506,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">effulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<collectingRegion box="[542,679,332,356]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="West New Britain" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">New Britain</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[694,892,332,356]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne 1987a</bibRefCitation>
<figureCitation box="[899,966,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,446,1857]" captionTargetId="figure-160@32.[164,1424,437,1861]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 8. Majority rule tree for larvae analysis. Tree shows the consensus of 4 MPTs of length 2245 from phylogenetic analysis of all characters for the 42 taxa scored for larval characters. New genera, new species, and still undescribed species in red. Showing the % of MPT over 50 %, above branches." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265358/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,151,1292]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,292,368,392]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Female.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[302,439,367,391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" metricValueMax="6.9" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" unit="mm" value="6.3" valueMax="6.9" valueMin="5.7">5.7–6.9 mm</quantity>
long. Colour: as for male except V5 sometimes paler brown than preceding ventrites, pale light orgn in V6, and the yellow semitransparent terminal two ventrites; basal abdominal tergites brown, T7, 8 paler brownish yellow than preceding ones. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[832,939,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–159" captionStartId="77.[151,263,1539,1562]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-182@77.[151,1436,193,1518]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 154–159. Medeopteryx spp. female abdomens ventral (not to scale) (ANIC). 154 M. antennata. 155 M. corusca (mating pair Catherine Mission). 156 M. cribellata (G381 mating pair). 157 M. effulgens (Kah New Ireland). 158 M. flagrans (G535). M. fulminea (Kar Kar Island)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265404/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Fig. 157</figureCitation>
): posterior margin of V6 not excavated, posterolateral corners rounded; V7 broadly, moderately deeply and evenly excavated along posterior margin, with posterolateral corners acutely angled and pointed; V8 not indented in median line. Bursa (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1256,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 160–167" captionStartId="78.[151,263,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,182,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-96@78.[177,1421,181,1849]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURES 160–167. Female Medeopteryx spp. bursa. 160 Medeopteryx antennata female of mating pair Sek Bridge (ANIC). 161, 162 M. corusca female of mating pair Kondiu (ANIC). 163 M. cribellata Kar Kar Island (ANIC). 164–167 M. similispupillae sp. nov. 164 bursa ventral; 165 reproductive system excluding ovaries lateral; 166 median oviduct plate ventral (anterior end to foot of page); 167 anterior plate lateral. Figure legends: 1 median oviduct plate; 2 posterior bursa plate; 3 anterior bursa plate; 4 spermatophore digesting gland." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265408/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Fig. 164</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,151,1292]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,548,572]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[324,542,548,572]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne (1987a)</bibRefCitation>
included only specimens with associated flashing data in the 
<typeStatus box="[1257,1305,548,572]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">type</typeStatus>
series, and indicated that assignment of specimens without flashing data was tentative only. Because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne" authorityYear="1987" box="[1179,1280,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effulgens">
<emphasis box="[1179,1280,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">effulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1338,1436,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminea">
<emphasis box="[1338,1436,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">fulminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar, determination of the colour patterns (especially those of head, MS and the terminal tergites) is important. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[275,491,655,679]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne (1987a)</bibRefCitation>
encountered difficulty determining colour patterns in alcohol preserved specimens, which were apparently dead before being preserved. This difficulty is sometimes overcome by drying specimens before examination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,151,1292]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne" authorityYear="1987" box="[199,338,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effulgens">
<emphasis box="[199,338,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">M. effulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an orange head with a dark triangular area on the vertex, and occur in New Britain. However 
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[151,375,799,823]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne (1987a)</bibRefCitation>
recorded one mating pair with an orange-headed male and black-headed female. No conclusions should be drawn from distributional records of specimens other than those of the 
<typeStatus box="[1242,1290,836,860]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">type</typeStatus>
series. 
<typeStatus box="[1380,1436,836,860]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne" authorityYear="1987" box="[311,412,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effulgens">
<emphasis box="[311,412,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">effulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[472,570,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminea">
<emphasis box="[472,570,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">fulminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not sympatric, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne" authorityYear="1987" box="[858,959,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effulgens">
<emphasis box="[858,959,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">effulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
restricted to New Britain while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1338,1436,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminea">
<emphasis box="[1338,1436,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">fulminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs on the New 
<collectingCountry box="[367,448,908,932]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Guinea</collectingCountry>
mainland. Although very similar morphologically, their light production is different.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,151,1292]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; McLean, M. R." box="[199,565,943,967]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="223 - 305" refId="ref122809" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; McLean, M. R. (1970) Revisional studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae: Luciolini). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 96, 223 - 305." type="journal article" year="1970">Ballantyne and McLean's (1970)</bibRefCitation>
composite 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1909" box="[694,918,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribellata">
<emphasis box="[694,918,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Pteroptyx cribellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included certain specimens with orange head; their Groups 1A, p. 244 and 1D, p. 244 were recorded from both New 
<collectingCountry box="[987,1068,980,1004]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and New Britain, and the New Guinean specimens are tentative inclusions here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,151,1292]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
In New Britain 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne" authorityYear="1987" box="[378,517,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effulgens">
<emphasis box="[378,517,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">M. effulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric with an orange-headed 
<taxonomicName authority="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2013" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[937,1262,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pharusaurea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[937,1262,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Australoluciola pharusaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1270,1360,1052,1076]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1270,1360,1052,1076]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lloyd, J. E." pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref127038" refString="Lloyd, J. E. (1973 a) Fireflies of Melanesia: Bioluminescence, Mating Behavior, and Synchronous flashing. Environmental Entomology, 2 (no. 6), 991 - 1008." type="journal article" year="1973">Lloyd (1973a)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 2 collecting sites &quot;SW of Simpson Harbor, on 
<collectingCountry box="[872,948,1088,1111]" name="Myanmar" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Burma</collectingCountry>
